If you’re using them as PWM controllers, the Spark class should be fine.

Here is my RobotBuilder module for CANSparkMax. Extract the folder to C:\Users<curr user>\Robotbuilder\extensions. Note I did not make the Java export module, only the C++. But you can easily fill in the Java Export.yaml.

CAN SparkMAX_1.0.1.zip (15.9 KB)

Hope this is helpful for anyone else in this situation!

Well I’m glad to be of some help here without even participating. For those who come accross this thread in the future our repository is found https://github.com/GraniteCityGearheads3244/RobotBuilderExtensions
Also included are some CTRE enhanced TalonSRX and TalonFX that add the Invert, Restore Factory Defaults, and a few other setting that are usually included in the CTRE sample code.

Just Download the repository, and unzip the contents into your wpilib installation folder usually found here on windows C:\Users\Public\wpilib"year"\Robotbuilder\extensions
